# PWA / desktop install (web prompt)

UnionOps offers desktop/app install via the **browser-native** Chromium “Install app” prompt (and Safari Add to Dock / Home Screen). There is **no** custom `beforeinstallprompt` UI.

## Surfaces

| Piece | Location |
|-------|----------|
| Manifest builder | `src/lib/pwa/manifest.ts` → `src/app/manifest.ts` (host defaults; cookie `uo_pwa_theme` can override `theme_color`) |
| Brand Kit → PWA chrome | `src/lib/pwa/brand-chrome.ts` via `BrandProvider` — live `theme-color` meta, replaces static `rel=icon` with branded SVG+32 PNG blobs, blob manifest + 192/512 icons |
| Host gate | `src/lib/pwa/hosts.ts` — apex `unionops.org` only (www stub is not installable until it redirects) |
| SW sync | `src/lib/pwa/register.ts` → `ServiceWorkerRegister` |
| Offline stub | `public/sw.js` — keep `CACHE`/`PRECACHE` in sync with `src/lib/pwa/shell.ts` |
| Quiet user guide | `/install` — Guides → About, footer nav peer, support/privacy cross-links |

## When changing PWA or related features

1. Update `src/lib/pwa/*` first; keep `public/sw.js` string-identical for cache/precache; bump `PWA_SHELL_CACHE` on policy changes.
2. Run `npm run test:unit` — must include `src/lib/pwa/*.test.ts` (hosts, register, manifest installability, shell↔sw sync, PC-safe policy, i18n).
3. If you touch `/install` chrome, keep it under Guides → About and/or footer (see `comms-public-nav.mdc`) — not a top-level Header peer of Tools.
4. Do **not** register the SW on localhost/CI; Playwright uses `serviceWorkers: "block"`.
5. Preserve installability: `name`/`short_name`, `start_url`, `display: standalone` (or fullscreen/minimal-ui), 192 + 512 icons.

## SW safety (PC / Edge installed app)

- **Navigate-only** `fetch` interception — never cache-first RSC/JS/API
- **`skipWaiting` yes, `clients.claim` no** — claim mid-load caused homescreen flash-reloads
- Serve `/sw.js` with `Cache-Control: no-cache` (`next.config.ts` / `vercel.json`)

## Do not

- Add an App Store / Microsoft Store wrapper without an explicit product decision
- Promote `/install` to a top-level Header link beside Tools (About group / footer only)
- Drop unit coverage when refactoring manifest, hosts, or `sw.js`
- Reintroduce `clients.claim()` or blanket `cache.put` without an explicit product decision
